BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:E2CgZyfOr086w0Rx5SZR6
SUMMARY:V.E. Schwab and Cat Clarke with Moira Macdonald
DTSTAMP:20260314T154442Z
DTSTART:20260406T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Layering classic tropes of the mystery genre with a clever mode
	rn satire of the publishing industry\\\, The Ending Writes Itself is the d
	ebut novel of “Evelyn Clarke\\\,” a new writing collaboration between best
	-selling authors V.E. Schwab and Cat Clarke. Joined in conversation by loc
	al author and journalist Moira Macdonald\\\, Schwab and Clarke explore the
	ir co-authoring venture and the twists and turns that await readers in the
	ir new take on a locked-room mystery thriller. How will the pages unfold f
	or the six authors isolated with nothing but their own minds\\\, a diaboli
	cal deadline\\\, and a plot-driving incentive? Starting is often the harde
	st part. But getting to the end could be murder. \\nWorld-renowned best-se
	lling novelist Arthur Fletch is a reclusive genius who captivates readers 
	with iconic protagonists and fiendish twists. So when six struggling autho
	rs of different genres receive an invitation to spend a weekend on his pri
	vate island off the coast of Scotland\\\, they pack their bags. But the tw
	ists have gone further than ever this time\\\, and the authors are greeted
	 with a shocking secret– Arthur Fletch is dead… and his highly-anticipated
	 last novel remains unfinished. \\nDesperate to publish\\\, Fletch’s agent
	 and editor have summoned these writers hoping one of them can pen a worth
	y ending. To sweeten the deal\\\, they pitch them the opportunity of a lif
	etime. Ghost write the final chapter and win an irresistible prize– a mind
	-boggling sum of money and a partnership that could relaunch their own car
	eers and guarantee future bestsellers. And with that to motivate them\\\, 
	surely 72 hours is enough time to finish Fletch’s magnus opus? All they ha
	ve to do is write…\n\nhttps://townhallseattle.org/event/ve-schwab-cat-clar
	ke/\n\nFrom Town Hall Seattle
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/ve-schwab-cat-clarke/
LOCATION:The Wyncote NW Forum\\\, 1119 8th Ave (Entrance off Seneca St.)\\\
	, Seattle\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:town-hall-seattle
CATEGORIES:Town Hall Seattle
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:c58g3n-BEGxctnoqWvKJZ
SUMMARY:Design for Longevity: ADUs and Aging in Place
DTSTAMP:20260314T154442Z
DTSTART:20260406T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Lili Weigert\\\, author of Making Space: ADUs for Modern L
	iving\\\, in conversation with local ADU designers Joe Schneider and Mike 
	Freeman of JAS Design Build. They will explore how thoughtful ADU design c
	an support aging in place\\\, foster intergenerational living\\\, and prov
	ide resilient housing options for the future. Rebecca Crichton\\\, Executi
	ve Director of Northwest Center for Creative Aging\\\, will moderate the d
	iscussion.\n\nhttps://townhallseattle.org/event/design-for-longevity/\n\nF
	rom Town Hall Seattle
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/design-for-longevity/
LOCATION:The Mehdi Reading Room\\\, 1119 8th Ave\\\, Seattle\\\, 98101\\\, 
	United States
